line-height:115%'>Sunday. &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:
115%'>Nobody in the Bible is pictured more vividly than the apostle Peter. His
growth from a rash fisherman into an unwavering witness for the Christian faith
offers a challenge to every disciple of Jesus. Early on, Jesus foreshadowed this
change when he changed his name from Simon to Cephas—a rock (Peter). (&lt;/span>&lt;span
style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%'>Read John &lt;b>1&lt;/b>:40-42&lt;/span>&lt;span
